1
00:00:09,760 --> 00:00:13,485
<i>Maybe I'm trying a little too hard.</i>

2
00:00:14,726 --> 00:00:19,258
<i>But then again, this one feels too plain.</i>

3
00:00:21,859 --> 00:00:25,740
<i>Wait, why am I overthinking?</i>

4
00:00:25,740 --> 00:00:28,780
<i>Just be normal. Normal is fine!</i>

5
00:00:30,501 --> 00:00:35,738
I've never even thought
about what Kazumi likes before.

6
00:01:33,605 --> 00:01:38,797
<i>This doesn't look like
I'm trying too hard, right?</i>

7
00:01:38,797 --> 00:01:42,047
<i>It's just Kazumi. Just Kazumi.</i>

8
00:01:42,047 --> 00:01:44,433
<i>So there's nothing to worry about.</i>

9
00:01:44,433 --> 00:01:45,795
Himari!

10
00:01:47,858 --> 00:01:54,026
<i>Damn it. Why does Kazumi
have to look so cool?</i>

11
00:01:56,119 --> 00:01:58,090
Hey there.

12
00:01:58,809 --> 00:02:01,917
- Did you wait for long?
- Not at all.

13
00:02:05,165 --> 00:02:06,882
You look cute today.

14
00:02:06,882 --> 00:02:09,409
Oh, thank you.

15
00:02:11,399 --> 00:02:14,057
I heard the pasta here is famous.

16
00:02:14,704 --> 00:02:16,282
This is their specialty.

17
00:02:16,282 --> 00:02:18,044
Wow, it looks delicious.

18
00:02:18,044 --> 00:02:19,688
What are you getting?

19
00:02:19,688 --> 00:02:21,347
Let's see...

20
00:02:21,347 --> 00:02:23,875
How about we order
different ones and share?

21
00:02:23,875 --> 00:02:26,666
Or we could get a pizza too.

22
00:02:26,666 --> 00:02:28,350
That sounds good.

23
00:02:28,350 --> 00:02:30,358
Then let's do that.

24
00:02:30,358 --> 00:02:31,786
Excuse me.

25
00:02:34,630 --> 00:02:38,137
<i>You know, now that I'm paying attention,</i>

26
00:02:38,137 --> 00:02:42,585
<i>Kazumi's taking the lead so naturally.</i>

27
00:02:42,585 --> 00:02:47,805
<i>I was so used to it
that I never even noticed.</i>

28
00:03:02,351 --> 00:03:04,397
<i>Why is this happening?</i>

29
00:03:07,206 --> 00:03:09,587
<i>He's shining.</i>

30
00:03:11,941 --> 00:03:13,401
Himari?

31
00:03:15,766 --> 00:03:20,046
For some reason, I can barely eat my pasta.

32
00:03:20,885 --> 00:03:22,840
My heart's racing.

33
00:03:24,092 --> 00:03:27,105
Seriously? You're overthinking it.

34
00:03:27,700 --> 00:03:29,444
Don't laugh at me!

35
00:03:29,444 --> 00:03:32,986
I know it's the same old you that I'm with.

36
00:03:32,986 --> 00:03:35,131
Sorry, sorry.

37
00:03:35,131 --> 00:03:36,667
I see.

38
00:03:37,514 --> 00:03:40,581
You make such cute faces on dates.

39
00:03:41,892 --> 00:03:43,480
Could you stop teasing me?

40
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:45,612
I'm not teasing you.

41
00:03:45,612 --> 00:03:47,388
I'm flirting.

42
00:03:49,327 --> 00:03:51,007
Don't look at me.

43
00:03:57,437 --> 00:03:59,871
It's beautiful!

44
00:03:59,871 --> 00:04:02,934
You love plants and flowers, right, Himari?

45
00:04:02,934 --> 00:04:07,662
I figured you could use some relaxation
after all the work stress.

46
00:04:07,662 --> 00:04:09,735
You know your stuff.

47
00:04:09,735 --> 00:04:12,105
I've known you for years, you know.

48
00:04:12,105 --> 00:04:15,382
Hey, aren't you embarrassed saying that?

49
00:04:15,382 --> 00:04:16,855
Not at all.

50
00:04:21,058 --> 00:04:22,816
Come here.

51
00:04:29,003 --> 00:04:32,386
It smells so nice here.

52
00:04:33,822 --> 00:04:36,828
What? Is there something on my face?

53
00:04:36,828 --> 00:04:40,172
You just look like you're having fun.

54
00:04:41,254 --> 00:04:45,440
You're right. I haven't had
a day off like this in a while.

55
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:57,032
By the way, do you remember
that flower bed back in college?

56
00:04:58,409 --> 00:05:01,668
Of course I do.

57
00:05:01,668 --> 00:05:05,693
We talked about everything there, didn't we?

58
00:05:05,693 --> 00:05:09,157
About assignments, the future...

59
00:05:10,246 --> 00:05:13,695
Or when to add soy sauce
to your raw egg over rice.

60
00:05:13,695 --> 00:05:15,969
Or asking me
to come on roller coasters with you

61
00:05:15,969 --> 00:05:17,624
because no one else would.

62
00:05:17,624 --> 00:05:21,565
No one else would ride
five or six times like you would.

63
00:05:21,565 --> 00:05:24,946
And I'd listen to you vent for hours on end.

64
00:05:24,946 --> 00:05:29,355
I don't just vent to anyone, you know.

65
00:05:30,757 --> 00:05:36,163
But I think all of that
is why we're so close now.

66
00:05:37,541 --> 00:05:42,294
Back then we were friends,
but now we're a couple.

67
00:05:42,294 --> 00:05:45,449
Hey, aren't you embarrassed saying that?

68
00:05:45,449 --> 00:05:47,109
Not at all.

69
00:05:50,523 --> 00:05:52,817
Since we're here, let's take a photo.

70
00:05:52,817 --> 00:05:54,157
Sure.

71
00:05:55,533 --> 00:05:57,433
- Here?
- Yeah.

72
00:05:58,431 --> 00:06:00,654
Is this angle good?

73
00:06:00,654 --> 00:06:03,329
- Ready?
- Would you like me to take one for you?

74
00:06:03,329 --> 00:06:05,214
Huh? Are you sure?

75
00:06:05,214 --> 00:06:06,497
Of course.

76
00:06:06,497 --> 00:06:09,294
- Thank you.
- Hold my bag, dear.

77
00:06:09,294 --> 00:06:10,769
- Okay.
- Thank you.

78
00:06:10,769 --> 00:06:11,935
Of course.

79
00:06:11,935 --> 00:06:13,775
Leave it to me.

80
00:06:13,775 --> 00:06:15,750
- Thank you very much.
- Thank you.

81
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:18,171
- Just hold still.
- Okay.

82
00:06:18,171 --> 00:06:20,313
How's this?

83
00:06:20,313 --> 00:06:21,984
Pull back a bit more,

84
00:06:21,984 --> 00:06:24,475
- and try lowering the camera.
- Okay.

85
00:06:24,475 --> 00:06:27,724
Like this? Oh, that looks nice.

86
00:06:27,724 --> 00:06:30,026
- Okay, I'll take it now.
- Okay.

87
00:06:30,026 --> 00:06:32,781
Say cheese.

88
00:06:34,924 --> 00:06:37,094
How is it? Does it look okay?

89
00:06:37,094 --> 00:06:40,396
- Oh, it looks great! Thank you so much.
- Thank you.

90
00:06:40,396 --> 00:06:42,178
I'm so glad.

91
00:06:42,178 --> 00:06:44,236
When I saw you two,

92
00:06:44,236 --> 00:06:48,686
it reminded me of my husband and me
when we were young.

93
00:06:48,686 --> 00:06:50,453
My heart fluttered.

94
00:06:50,453 --> 00:06:51,933
Thank you.

95
00:06:51,933 --> 00:06:55,761
We used to go on dates in places like this.

96
00:06:55,761 --> 00:06:57,053
- Really?
- I see.

97
00:06:57,053 --> 00:06:59,625
That was 30 years ago now.

98
00:06:59,625 --> 00:07:04,139
30 years! You've been together all this time!

99
00:07:04,139 --> 00:07:08,400
Thank you. I'm sure you two will be the same.

100
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:11,081
You make such a lovely couple.

101
00:07:11,081 --> 00:07:12,903
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you.

102
00:07:12,903 --> 00:07:14,710
Goodbye then.

103
00:07:23,740 --> 00:07:25,987
She said we'll be like them.

104
00:07:27,315 --> 00:07:28,968
Let's go.

105
00:07:33,641 --> 00:07:38,329
Wow, it's so beautiful!

106
00:07:38,329 --> 00:07:41,634
Yeah, the whole place is lit up.

107
00:07:41,634 --> 00:07:43,434
Right?

108
00:07:52,365 --> 00:07:53,878
Himari.

109
00:07:55,046 --> 00:07:59,938
How did it feel,
spending the whole day together as lovers?

110
00:08:03,683 --> 00:08:05,010
Right.

111
00:08:14,791 --> 00:08:19,864
If you don't have an answer yet,
you can tell me later.

112
00:08:23,731 --> 00:08:27,226
If it's hard to say face-to-face,
a text is fine too.

113
00:08:27,994 --> 00:08:30,207
Take it at your own pace.

114
00:08:33,077 --> 00:08:35,183
<i>He's always been this way.</i>

115
00:08:35,851 --> 00:08:40,606
<i>He always says what I want to hear,</i>

116
00:08:40,606 --> 00:08:45,473
<i>and he always asks what I want to do.</i>

117
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:53,335
<i>I don't think this relationship will change
even if we become a couple.</i>

118
00:08:54,304 --> 00:08:58,832
<i>I don't need to be afraid at all.</i>

119
00:08:59,843 --> 00:09:01,397
Kazumi.

120
00:09:04,061 --> 00:09:05,696
I...

121
00:09:06,668 --> 00:09:09,271
I like you too.

122
00:09:13,571 --> 00:09:15,751
I want us to be together forever.

123
00:09:17,711 --> 00:09:19,333
That means...

124
00:09:21,708 --> 00:09:22,950
Yeah.

125
00:09:23,967 --> 00:09:26,467
I'll be in your care.

126
00:09:39,045 --> 00:09:40,518
Himari.

127
00:09:43,141 --> 00:09:47,191
This is... so embarrassing.

128
00:09:48,707 --> 00:09:50,360
Yeah.

129
00:10:24,464 --> 00:10:28,690
Whatever you want me to do, I'll do it.

130
00:10:30,012 --> 00:10:33,730
So can you tell me, for my sake?

131
00:10:35,774 --> 00:10:40,209
<i>I know he's saying this
so I'll be honest with him.</i>

132
00:10:55,815 --> 00:10:58,908
You really are adorable, Himari.

133
00:11:00,515 --> 00:11:07,085
<i>Kazumi's words melt my thoughts into a haze.</i>

134
00:11:08,382 --> 00:11:14,645
<i>His every gesture fills my heart completely.</i>

135
00:11:40,520 --> 00:11:45,447
<i>Kazumi makes faces like this too?</i>

136
00:11:47,037 --> 00:11:52,253
<i>I can't tell where my body ends
and his begins,</i>

137
00:11:52,253 --> 00:11:55,745
<i>or which part belongs to who.</i>

138
00:11:55,745 --> 00:11:59,667
<i>We're completely entangled.</i>

139
00:12:11,083 --> 00:12:15,073
<i>I never knew how fulfilling it was to give in</i>

140
00:12:15,073 --> 00:12:18,097
<i>without any worries.</i>

141
00:12:44,746 --> 00:12:48,767
<i>I don't know how to put
this feeling into words.</i>

142
00:12:48,767 --> 00:12:51,296
<i>I feel like sprinting right now,</i>

143
00:12:51,296 --> 00:12:54,787
<i>or clinging to her and crying.</i>

144
00:13:02,938 --> 00:13:06,905
<i>I felt like I shouldn't touch her
with these dirty hands.</i>

145
00:13:06,905 --> 00:13:09,278
<i>But that's not right.</i>

146
00:13:15,530 --> 00:13:18,720
<i>If someone else is going to pluck you,</i>

147
00:13:18,720 --> 00:13:21,134
<i>I'd rather you bloom by my side.</i>

148
00:13:32,461 --> 00:13:34,701
<i>As long as I have you,</i>

149
00:13:34,701 --> 00:13:37,201
<i>I don't need anything else in life.</i>

150
00:13:51,535 --> 00:13:53,722
Good morning, Himari.

151
00:13:59,649 --> 00:14:01,143
Morning.

152
00:14:01,981 --> 00:14:04,662
I feel kinda shy right now.

153
00:14:16,435 --> 00:14:18,698
There are flowers here.

154
00:14:18,698 --> 00:14:21,020
I never noticed.

155
00:14:22,473 --> 00:14:25,971
This one's from that flower bed.

156
00:14:26,601 --> 00:14:28,991
They let me have it,

157
00:14:28,991 --> 00:14:31,478
and I've cared for it ever since.

158
00:14:32,891 --> 00:14:35,371
I see.

159
00:14:35,371 --> 00:14:40,939
So it's been by your side all this time, huh?

160
00:14:57,176 --> 00:15:02,969
<i>Now that I take a closer look,
his room is really tidy.</i>

161
00:15:11,613 --> 00:15:13,773
I've never seen this before.

162
00:15:20,231 --> 00:15:26,998
<i>His mom is so beautiful,
and his dad seems so refined.</i>

163
00:15:26,998 --> 00:15:31,882
<i>His little brother is so cute too.</i>

164
00:15:42,246 --> 00:15:44,006
His mom.
[Mom]

165
00:15:58,529 --> 00:16:03,551
<i>I wonder what Kazumi's family is like.</i>

166
00:16:06,577 --> 00:16:09,910
<i>Wait, am I going to be okay?</i>

167
00:16:09,910 --> 00:16:14,798
<i>What if they tell me
I'm not good enough for Kazumi?</i>

168
00:16:14,798 --> 00:16:16,177
What's wrong?

169
00:16:16,177 --> 00:16:19,130
Oh, nothing.

170
00:16:19,130 --> 00:16:22,678
Your mom called earlier.

171
00:16:22,678 --> 00:16:24,605
You should call her.

172
00:16:25,442 --> 00:16:29,776
Thanks. But don't worry about it.
I'll call her later.

173
00:16:30,470 --> 00:16:32,684
You should go shower too.

174
00:16:32,684 --> 00:16:35,711
Sure, I'll take one then.

175
00:16:43,250 --> 00:16:45,990
[Vextos]

176
00:16:51,435 --> 00:16:52,787
Got a cold?

177
00:16:52,787 --> 00:16:55,268
No, I'm fine.

178
00:16:56,023 --> 00:17:01,920
<i>Maybe I dressed too lightly yesterday
at Kazumi's place.</i>

179
00:17:02,560 --> 00:17:06,032
Shibasaki, are you dating Hojo?

180
00:17:06,032 --> 00:17:07,386
Huh?

181
00:17:08,695 --> 00:17:10,617
We're not dating!

182
00:17:11,299 --> 00:17:13,870
We're just close.

183
00:17:13,870 --> 00:17:16,003
Sure.

184
00:17:16,003 --> 00:17:20,851
<i>Phew, that was close! Did he believe me?</i>

185
00:17:22,327 --> 00:17:24,508
About Hojo...

186
00:17:24,508 --> 00:17:27,505
I bet he's from a wealthy family.

187
00:17:28,480 --> 00:17:30,054
Why's that?

188
00:17:30,855 --> 00:17:34,186
Well, he just hasn't talked about them much.

189
00:17:35,754 --> 00:17:38,089
He was born in Tokyo, I think.

190
00:17:38,089 --> 00:17:40,217
Where in Tokyo?

191
00:17:41,199 --> 00:17:43,332
That's...

192
00:17:44,367 --> 00:17:47,564
<i>Actually, I don't know.</i>

193
00:17:47,564 --> 00:17:51,340
<i>I don't know where Kazumi was born,</i>

194
00:17:51,340 --> 00:17:57,665
<i>what school he went to,
or what kind of kid he was...</i>

195
00:17:57,665 --> 00:17:59,784
You don't know?

196
00:18:01,333 --> 00:18:05,925
I guess I never
really asked about that stuff.

197
00:18:05,925 --> 00:18:09,078
After being friends for so long?

198
00:18:14,732 --> 00:18:19,987
Hojo gets along with everyone,

199
00:18:19,987 --> 00:18:23,122
but I guess he's got secrets, huh?

200
00:18:23,122 --> 00:18:26,464
Well, I'm not sure.

201
00:18:28,788 --> 00:18:32,194
I just feel some distance from him.

202
00:18:32,194 --> 00:18:34,724
Like he's hiding his real self.

203
00:18:36,068 --> 00:18:39,420
I don't think so, but...

204
00:18:44,372 --> 00:18:46,906
Isn't your cold getting worse?

205
00:18:46,906 --> 00:18:48,246
Huh?

206
00:18:50,719 --> 00:18:52,180
It definitely is.

207
00:18:52,180 --> 00:18:53,992
I'm fine, I'm fine.

208
00:18:53,992 --> 00:18:55,430
I'll just...

209
00:18:55,430 --> 00:18:56,896
Whoa!

210
00:18:56,896 --> 00:18:59,242
You should lie down for a bit.

211
00:18:59,242 --> 00:19:00,455
Follow me.

212
00:19:00,455 --> 00:19:01,869
You're right.

213
00:19:01,869 --> 00:19:03,922
Don't push yourself.

214
00:19:04,559 --> 00:19:06,719
- Are you okay?
- I'm fine.

215
00:19:07,855 --> 00:19:10,568
Sorry, Nihei...

216
00:19:11,492 --> 00:19:13,647
I told Hojo too.

217
00:19:13,647 --> 00:19:17,661
You don't seem like the type
to ask for a break yourself.

218
00:19:17,661 --> 00:19:19,188
Thank you.

219
00:19:20,067 --> 00:19:22,588
You're really kind, Nihei.

220
00:19:22,588 --> 00:19:24,505
Huh?

221
00:19:24,505 --> 00:19:27,524
Th-That's not true.

222
00:19:31,854 --> 00:19:34,081
I'm really sorry for troubling you.

223
00:19:34,081 --> 00:19:36,118
But you can go now.

224
00:19:36,118 --> 00:19:37,922
Don't worry about it.

225
00:19:37,922 --> 00:19:40,452
You always do
this kind of thing for everyone.

226
00:19:40,452 --> 00:19:42,642
Sorry if I'm overstepping.

227
00:19:43,663 --> 00:19:46,263
You're such a good person.

228
00:19:51,872 --> 00:19:55,717
I'll go grab some water.
Just stay put and rest.

229
00:19:55,717 --> 00:19:57,277
Thanks.

230
00:20:00,938 --> 00:20:05,279
Nihei, how's Shibasaki doing?

231
00:20:06,174 --> 00:20:09,693
She seems to have a fever.
She's sleeping now.

232
00:20:09,693 --> 00:20:12,308
I see. Thanks.

233
00:20:12,988 --> 00:20:15,929
I called a taxi. It should be here soon.

234
00:20:15,929 --> 00:20:18,544
You can head back to work now.

235
00:20:20,295 --> 00:20:23,037
Okay, thank you.

236
00:20:25,120 --> 00:20:29,003
Thank you for looking out for her.

237
00:20:31,464 --> 00:20:32,997
Not at all.

238
00:20:34,637 --> 00:20:37,502
I heard you've been friends since college.

239
00:20:38,837 --> 00:20:40,683
That's right.

240
00:20:40,683 --> 00:20:43,661
We've known each other a long time now.

241
00:20:44,871 --> 00:20:49,228
And yet, you haven't told her much
about yourself, huh?

242
00:20:52,860 --> 00:20:54,740
What do you mean?

243
00:20:56,807 --> 00:20:59,189
I'll be blunt.

244
00:20:59,189 --> 00:21:03,332
I don't think how long
you've known someone really matters.

245
00:21:03,332 --> 00:21:07,699
It's hard to get along with someone
if they have too many secrets.

246
00:21:10,970 --> 00:21:13,950
If it were me, I'd tell her everything.

247
00:21:40,545 --> 00:21:46,371
<i>It's been a while
since I've had a fever this bad.</i>

248
00:21:46,371 --> 00:21:50,115
<i>Yeah, I was in elementary school.</i>

249
00:21:50,115 --> 00:21:54,467
<i>When I got sick,
my dad had to take time off work,</i>

250
00:21:54,467 --> 00:22:00,757
<i>so I didn't want to be a bother,
and pretended I was fine on my own.</i>

251
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:42,235
[Vextos]

252
00:22:43,069 --> 00:22:44,684
Fukuoka?

253
00:22:44,684 --> 00:22:49,501
Yes, the Fukuoka branch
needs extra help on short notice.

254
00:22:49,501 --> 00:22:53,911
I was wondering if you could
take on the assignment.

255
00:23:45,526 --> 00:23:48,703
You're good at controlling people,
aren't you, Hojo?

256
00:23:48,703 --> 00:23:50,939
You make me sound like some kind of villain.

257
00:23:50,939 --> 00:23:53,849
Your parents must be wonderful people too.

258
00:23:53,849 --> 00:23:55,517
It's because I like you.

259
00:23:55,517 --> 00:23:56,638
